      "message": "Maybe a comment explaining why we chose each of these, saying that we’re…less sure than we usually are? (Because we usually shoot for 100%.)\n\nI have half a mind to set up a really old kernel in a VM to see what happens. But only half a mind.\n\nIt’s easier to just pass a bogus bit into a contemporary kernel, see that it results in EINVAL (or whatever), and hope that old kernels did the same.",
